  id: evt_rosa_06
  characterId: stk_rosa
  title: Gaming the Safety Net
  bodyText: "People are learning how your system works. Not everyone - but enough.
    They delay reporting income. They structure jobs to stay just below thresholds.
    They time applications to trigger higher priority. Some of this is survival.
    Some of it is exploitation. Your system can\u2019t tell the difference."
  choiceA:
    label: Tighten detection and close loopholes
    flavor: We reduce abuse.
    outcome: Abuse drops noticeably. Legitimate users feel increased pressure and
      scrutiny.
    effects:
      industry: 2
      civilSociety: -1
      governance: 2
      innovation: 0
  choiceB:
    label: Accept some gaming to protect the vulnerable
    flavor: We tolerate misuse.
    outcome: Fewer people are wrongly penalized. System costs and inefficiencies
      grow.
    effects:
      industry: -1
      civilSociety: 3
      governance: 0
      innovation: 1
